Adobe Acrobat Reader  XI 11.0.23 {Latest} - 2017



Adobe Reader provides basic functions when working with PDF documents, such as copying, browsing, printing, managing images, page transformation (orientation), and so on. Supports all technical features of the implementation of the latest versions of PDF (for example, the output of a three-dimensional image within a document).

Features of Adobe Reader:
· Ability to view, manipulate and comment on 3D content of documents created with the help of Acrobat Adobe 3D software.
· Scaling of the selected sections of the document.
· Play multimedia content (text, graphic, audio and video files), read and organize e-books. Playback of the QuickTime, Macromedia Flash, Real and Windows Media files built into documents.
· Allows you to work with the document through forms.
· Ability to search the Internet directly from the Adobe Reader interface.
· Additional module (plug-in) to the browser. Support for Netscape, Firefox, and Mozilla (for Windows only).
· Print documents via wireless networks.
· Organization of on-line video conferences.
· Safe technologies. Digital signatures for PDF documents.
· Start Meeting function, which allows several people to work on the document at the same time.
· Tools to facilitate work for people with impaired vision.
